body:
Underrated YouTube channels

Just for fun!

ClickForTaz:

She’s so bright, happy and creative. Always positive and has interesting challenges and videos. Check out one of her video about going on a 5 euro flight to Italy if you’re looking for a good time.

Report of the Week

At once strange and highly comedic, it remains unclear whether he plays a character or is truly an enigma (both of which may be true). While dressing in 80s and 90s oversized suits, looking dapper and being articulate, he reviews mostly fast food. Don’t be fooled, though. He also graces us with tutorials and day in the life style vlogs. Almost all his videos are one take, and it seems more like a performance than simply a YouTube video.

Different Russia:

She shows us her daily life in Russia. Over time, you get to know her family – her husband and son (both named Alex) are interesting to meet and her videos give you an everyday view on life in Russia. Simplistic and wholesome.

Agenda Free TV:

Steve reports live on news events. If mainstream media is covering other things, you can be sure to catch an in depth, as it happens analysis from Steve on whichever topic he is covering.

Chase Amie:

Clad with 50k in designer handbags, her fashion tutorials are mesmerizing and make you want to purchase your own Chanel bag.

Oliver the Beagle:

His name is Oliver and he is a beagle.

The Retro Future:

Watch someone take apart older tech and put it back together. Like asmr, but for your eyes.

Alexa Lexie:

Does wonderful edits, mostly of Star Wars and other assorted fandoms.

Uni Vloggers

Izzy Snapshots:

A student at Columbia University’s Barnard College, she shares her journey to acceptance at Columbia and her first year at Fordham. At first a dance major, she switch to Columbia economics in her second year. A real life look at NYC student living at a top tier university.

Holly Gabrielle:

A final year Biology student at Cambridge, Holly shares mostly study tips and her life as a vegan. Doing what the average person does in a week in one day, you’ll be tired after watching her be more productive than you can ever hope to be. Candid about her past struggles with anorexia and mental health as it relates to academia, she shares unique young female viewpoints on dating every Valentine’s Day as well as her average day in the life videos.

Miss Varz:

A second year student at Oxford, Miss Varz shared her academic journey, and how it isn’t always linear. At first accepted to Oxford for a foundation year, and later accepted as an anthropology major, she points out the importance of Black admittance to high ranking schools in the UK (or lack thereof). As a voice that points out a lack of racial diversity in Oxford, her videos showcase her concerns and help students who are feeling that it might just not be “worth applying”. She is also friends with Malala, and Malala appears in many of her videos for both interviews and games.

Ruby Granger:

A first year student at Exeter, she has shared her study and organization tips all throughout her highschool years. Positive and unapologetically herself, she shares both her disappointments and victories on camera (like being rejected from Oxford). Currently studying Religion, she talks about her path to get to where she is now and is highly focused on her academic work.

Unjaded Jade

Currently taking a gap year between A levels and University (at Bristol), Jade shares her life as a vegan. Experience oriented, her videos showcase her Gap Year (much like what Jacksgap was supposed to be, if you rememeber that!) She has been interviewed by many British newsources and made TV appearances about what it means to be a “studytuber”.

body:
I genuinely wish Tati and James Wesbrook the best going forward from now.

As well as Heidi and Ross. Its been a wild week for YouTube.

Now if you’re in need of some currently less drama involved people in similar YouTube spaces, I have some suggestions.

Make-up:

SimplyNailogical / SimplyNotLogical

Mia Maples

Safiya Nygaard

Corrine Leigh / Threadbanger (not family friendly)

Let’s Plays & Lists

GillyTheKid

JohnWolfe / JohnTwolfe ( please talk to me about rusty lake )

Mr.Kravin

ConnorTheWaffle

RabbidLuigi

BrutalMoose / moose2

Caddicarus

(Note: Ian and Caddy are a part of HiddenBlock, almost a sister thing to NormalBoots, so be aware you may still see Jared in older vids if they’ve left them up.)

Feel free to add to the list ! And as you can see I watch a lot more stuff about video games than I do make-up, sorry XD
